# COSMOS — Interactive Physics Presentation
## Claude.md — Project Brief for Claude Code

---

## 1. PROJECT OVERVIEW

**What this is:** A scrollytelling interactive website about galaxies and the universe, built as a physics school presentation. This is also a flagship portfolio piece.

**Presentation context:** A teacher walks through pre-defined topics in order. The site must follow that flow exactly — scrolling reveals sections in sequence. The experience must feel like a cinematic space journey, not a PowerPoint.

**Stack:**
- HTML5
- CSS3 + SASS/SCSS
- Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+)
- Three.js (via CDN, no npm, no build tools)
- GSAP + ScrollTrigger (via CDN) for scroll animations

**No frameworks. No npm. Everything runs from a single `index.html` opened locally in a browser.**

---

## 2. VISUAL DIRECTION

**Aesthetic:** Dark, cinematic, space-grade. Think NASA meets Apple product page.

**Color palette:**
- Background: `#020408` (near-black, deep space)
- Primary accent: `#4FC3F7` (cold blue, star light)
- Secondary accent: `#E8D5B7` (warm gold, nebula)
- Text: `#E8EAF0` (off-white)
- Subtle glow: `rgba(79, 195, 247, 0.15)`

**Typography:**
- Display/headings: `Orbitron` (Google Fonts) — geometric, futuristic
- Body text: `Inter` or `DM Sans` — readable, modern
- Section labels: `Space Mono` — monospace terminal feel

**Atmosphere:**
- Starfield background (animated CSS or Three.js particles) — always visible
- Parallax depth on scroll
- Sections fade/slide in as they enter viewport
- Subtle nebula glow effects behind content cards
- No white backgrounds anywhere. Everything is transparent over space.

---

## 3. SITE STRUCTURE & SECTIONS

The site is a single long-scroll page. Each section maps to a teacher's curriculum topic.

```
[INTRO / HERO]
      ↓
[SECTION 1 — The Universe]
      ↓
[SECTION 2 — Galaxies Overview]
      ↓
[SECTION 3 — The Milky Way] → INTERACTIVE: click to explore
      ↓
[SECTION 4 — Our Solar System] → INTERACTIVE: 3D planets
      ↓
[SECTION 5 — Voyager] → INTERACTIVE: animated probe
      ↓
[QUIZ]
      ↓
[OUTRO]
```

---

## 4. SECTION SPECIFICATIONS

### HERO
- Full-screen, animated starfield background (Three.js particles or CSS)
- Large centered title: **"COSMOS"** with subtle glow animation
- Subtitle: "O călătorie interactivă prin Univers"
- Scroll-down indicator (animated arrow or text)
- No navigation bar — pure immersion

---

### SECTION 1 — Universul
**Content:** What is the universe, scale, age, composition  
**Layout:** Text card (left) + visual (right) — nebula image or generated visual  
**Animation:** Fade in on scroll (ScrollTrigger)  
**Data to include:**
- Vârsta: ~13.8 miliarde ani
- Diametru observabil: ~93 miliarde ani-lumină
- Compoziție: 68% energie întunecată, 27% materie întunecată, 5% materie obișnuită

---

### SECTION 2 — Galaxii
**Content:** Types of galaxies (spiral, elliptical, irregular), examples  
**Layout:** Horizontal scroll cards OR grid of galaxy types  
**Animation:** Cards slide in from sides on scroll  
**Interactive:** Hover over each galaxy type = info tooltip  
**Examples to include:**
- Calea Lactee (spiral)
- Andromeda (spiral)
- Centaurus A (elliptical)
- Magellanic Clouds (irregular)

---

### SECTION 3 — Calea Lactee
**Content:** Our galaxy — structure, size, position of Solar System  
**Layout:** Full-width section with overhead galaxy map  
**THE KEY INTERACTION:**
- Display a top-down 2D illustration of the Milky Way (CSS/canvas, or SVG)
- A glowing dot marks our Solar System's position (Orion Arm)
- User clicks the dot → smooth zoom/transition → Section 4 (Solar System) loads or appears
- If full zoom transition is too complex: animated scroll-to with camera pan effect  
**Data to include:**
- Diametru: ~100,000 ani-lumină
- Număr stele estimate: 100-400 miliarde
- Tipul brațului nostru: Brațul Orion (minor)
- Distanța de la centru: ~26,000 ani-lumină

---

### SECTION 4 — Sistemul Solar (THREE.JS CORE FEATURE)
**This is the centerpiece of the project.**

**Layout:** Three.js canvas takes 60-70% of the screen. Info panel on the right.

**3D Scene:**
- Dark space background (match site bg)
- Sun at center — emissive yellow/orange sphere with glow shader
- All 8 planets in correct relative order (not to scale — too hard to see)
- Each planet: textured sphere using NASA texture maps
- Planets orbit the Sun continuously (slow, elegant)
- OrbitControls enabled — user can drag to rotate the whole scene

**Planet textures (NASA free):**
```
Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn (+ rings), Uranus, Neptune
```

**Planet interaction:**
- Click on any planet → orbit camera zooms to that planet
- Info panel updates with:
  - Planet name (large)
  - Key facts: diameter, distance from Sun, orbital period, number of moons, surface temperature
  - 1-2 interesting facts

**UI controls:**
- Small "Reset View" button to return to full system view
- Planet names always visible as floating labels (CSS sprites above each planet)

**Saturn specifically:** Must have visible ring system (Three.js RingGeometry)

---

### SECTION 5 — Voyager
**Content:** Voyager 1 mission — humanity's farthest spacecraft

**Layout:** Semi-dark section, Milky Way edge illustration in background

**Animation:**
- Animated trajectory line from Earth toward edge of Solar System
- Small Voyager probe model (simple geometric shape or SVG) travels along the line
- Line reveals progressively as it animates (DrawSVG or JS path animation)
- Probe arrives at edge of heliosphere → blinks, text appears: "Spațiu interstelar"

**Clickable probe:**
When user clicks Voyager:
- Modal or side panel opens
- Shows: launch date (Sept 5, 1977), current distance (~24 billion km from Sun), speed (~17 km/s), mission status, what it carries (Golden Record)

**Data to display:**
- Lansare: 5 septembrie 1977
- Distanța actuală: ~24 miliarde km de Soare (actualizată periodic)
- Viteza: ~17 km/s (61,200 km/h)
- A ieșit din heliosferă: 25 august 2012
- Conține: Discul de Aur — mesaje, muzică, sunete de pe Pământ

---

### QUIZ
**Mechanic:** Free text input — substring matching (case-insensitive)

**Format:**
- 5-7 questions, one at a time
- Question displayed in center
- Input field below
- Submit button OR Enter key to confirm
- Correct: green flash + next question
- Wrong: red flash + retry allowed (or show correct answer after 2 attempts)
- Final score screen at the end

**Sample questions:**
```
1. "Care este vârsta aproximativă a Universului?" → ["13.8", "13,8"]
2. "Cum se numește galaxia noastră?" → ["calea lactee", "lactee"]
3. "Câte planete are Sistemul Solar?" → ["8", "opt"]
4. "Ce misiune a ieșit primul din Sistemul Solar?" → ["voyager"]
5. "Ce tip de galaxie este Calea Lactee?" → ["spirală", "spirala"]
6. "Câte miliarde de stele conține aproximativ Calea Lactee?" → ["100", "200", "400"]
```

**UI:** Dark card, monospace font for input, progress indicator (1/6, 2/6...)

---

### OUTRO
- Simple dark screen
- Text: "Universul nu are capăt. Curiozitatea ta nici atât."
- Small credits line
- Optional: "Apasă orice tastă pentru a relua" → returns to top

---

