## 6. TECHNICAL NOTES FOR CLAUDE CODE

### Three.js setup (CDN only):
```html
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/three.js/r128/three.min.js"></script>
```

Note: `THREE.OrbitControls` is NOT included in r128 core. Load separately:
```html
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/three@0.128.0/examples/js/controls/OrbitControls.js"></script>
```

### GSAP setup (CDN):
```html
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.12.2/gsap.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.12.2/ScrollTrigger.min.js"></script>
```

### Performance rules:
- The Three.js canvas runs only when Section 4 is in viewport (pause renderer otherwise)
- Use `requestAnimationFrame` correctly — cancel when tab is hidden
- Textures: compress JPGs to under 1MB each before loading
- No texture loading in a loop — preload all at init

### SASS compilation:
- Use VS Code Live Sass Compiler extension or `sass --watch style/main.scss:css/main.css`
- All colors and fonts defined only in `_variables.scss`

### Compatibility:
- Must work on Chrome (latest) — presentation will be on Chrome
- No IE support needed
- Mobile not priority — this is a desktop school presentation

