## 8. BUILD ORDER (for Claude Code — do in this order)

1. `index.html` scaffold + CDN links
2. `_variables.scss` + `_reset.scss` + basic layout
3. Starfield background (JS particles)
4. Hero section (static, animated title)
5. Sections 1 & 2 (text + scroll animations)
6. Milky Way map (Section 3) — click interaction
7. Solar System — Three.js scene (Section 4) — this is the hardest part
8. Voyager animation (Section 5)
9. Quiz logic
10. Polish: transitions, glow effects, typography refinement
11. Outro

**Do NOT jump ahead. Each step must work before moving to the next.**

---

## 9. WHAT SUCCESS LOOKS LIKE

A person who knows nothing about coding opens this on a laptop and says "wow."

A physics teacher sees the scientific content is correct and complete.

A developer looks at the GitHub repo and sees clean, structured code with no spaghetti.

You can present this confidently because you understand every line.

